# MarketLens Project Structure

## Path aliases

- **`@/*`** → `src/*` (e.g. `@/components/...`, `@/lib/utils`, `@/actions/...`)
- **`@/server/*`** → `src/server/*` (e.g. `@/server/services/...`, `@/server/api/...`)

Use these in imports; avoid relative paths that cross major boundaries.

---

## High-level layout

```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router (routes + layouts)
├── components/             # UI: features, ui, common
├── actions/                # Server Actions ('use server')
├── server/                 # Backend-only (services, repos, models, api helpers)
├── lib/                    # Shared frontend utils (e.g. cn)
├── config/                 # Env and app config
├── types/                  # Shared TS types
├── constants/              # App constants
├── hooks/                  # Shared React hooks
├── stores/                 # Zustand (client state)
└── middleware.ts           # Next.js middleware
```

**Rule:** Route Handlers in `app/api/` and Server Actions in `actions/` call into `server/`. Client components and pages only import from `app/`, `components/`, `actions/`, `lib/utils`, `types/`, `config/`, `hooks/`, `stores/` — not from `server/` directly.

---

## app/ (App Router)

- **`app/page.tsx`** — Landing (marketing). Root `/`.
- **`app/layout.tsx`** — Root layout (html, body, globals).
- **`app/(auth)/`** — Route group (no URL segment). e.g. `(auth)/login` → `/login`.
- **`app/dashboard/`** — Dashboard segment. `/dashboard` = Overview; layout wraps sidebar + main.
- **`app/dashboard/actions/`** — Actions hub. `/dashboard/actions`, `/dashboard/actions/competitor-radar`, `/dashboard/actions/compliance`.
- **`app/dashboard/status`**, **information**, **insights** — Other dashboard pages.
- **`app/api/`** — Route Handlers only. `api/health`, `api/v1/auth/...`, `api/v1/users/...`, `api/v1/scan/run`, `api/v1/compliance`, `api/v1/webhooks/stripe`.

Add new pages under the correct segment (e.g. new dashboard page under `app/dashboard/`). Use route groups like `(auth)` only when you want a shared layout without adding a path segment.

---

## components/

- **`components/ui/`** — Aceternity (`aceternity/`), primitives, shadcn. Reusable UI building blocks.
- **`components/features/`** — Feature-specific UI and hooks:
  - **`competitor-radar/`** — CompetitorRadarView, CompetitorManageView, cards, feed, modals, types.
  - **`compliance-radar/`** — Compliance UI (e.g. CircularFeed, CircularCard).
  - **`dashboard/`** — DashboardNav (sidebar with nested Actions), other dashboard widgets.
  - **`landing/`** — LandingHero, LandingFeatures, LandingNav.
  - **`integrations/`** — Jira, Linear, RuleBuilder.
- **`components/common/`** — Shared composite components.

Prefer one primary component per file; co-locate feature types/hooks in the same feature folder.

---

## actions/

Server Actions only (`'use server'`). One file per domain (e.g. `competitor.actions.ts`, `scan.actions.ts`, `users.actions.ts`). They call `@/server/services/...` or `@/server/repositories/...`; never put DB or heavy logic in the action file itself.

---

## server/ (backend-only)

- **`server/api/`** — Route handler wrapper, HTTP errors, response helpers, middleware (auth, rateLimit, validate).
- **`server/lib/`** — db, redis, logger, auth, tinyfish client and goals.
- **`server/services/`** — Business logic (scan, change-detection, enrichment, action, users, auth, email).
- **`server/repositories/`** — DB access (Mongoose); used by services.
- **`server/models/`** — Mongoose schemas/models.

Route Handlers live under `app/api/` and import from `@/server/...`. Do not import `server/` from client components or from `lib/` (except shared `lib/utils` etc. used by both).

---

## lib/, config/, types/, constants/, hooks/, stores/

- **`lib/`** — Currently `utils.ts` (e.g. `cn()`). Shared, non-server-only helpers used by components.
- **`config/`** — Env and app config (e.g. Zod-validated env).
- **`types/`** — Shared TypeScript types (e.g. `actions.types.ts`).
- **`constants/`** — App-wide constants.
- **`hooks/`** — Shared React hooks.
- **`stores/`** — Zustand stores (client-only state).

Keep these free of server-only code; they are part of the frontend-safe surface.

---

## Where to put new code

| What you're adding              | Place in |
|----------------------------------|----------|
| New page/route                   | `app/<segment>/page.tsx` (or under `dashboard/`, `(auth)/`, etc.) |
| New API endpoint                 | `app/api/v1/.../route.ts` |
| New reusable UI piece            | `components/ui/` (aceternity, primitives, shadcn) |
| New feature UI + state           | `components/features/<feature-name>/` |
| New Server Action                | `actions/<domain>.actions.ts` |
| New business logic               | `server/services/` |
| New DB access                    | `server/repositories/` + `server/models/` if needed |
| New shared type                  | `types/` or next to feature in `components/features/...` |
| New shared util (non-server)     | `lib/` (e.g. `lib/utils.ts`) |
